{
  "texts": [
    "Before using ABCD, we had to perform a round of coarse alignment for two reasons.",
    "First, the rigidly registered sections contained a large number of section-wide scale changes.",
    "As scale changes are non-rigid transformations, they would be penalized by the elastic regularizer used in SEAMLeSS and lead to poor image pair alignment quality.",
    "Moreover, because many of FAFB islands were overlapping after the rigid registration, each section was represented with several images, one per island, to avoid data loss.",
    "This posed an operational challenge for our implementation of ABCD, as it only supported aligning stacks of single images, not sets of potentially overlapping images."
  ]
}